hush-vani-weights

This crate redistributes the model weights of "Hush" by Weya AI:

    https://huggingface.co/weya-ai/hush

The Hush model is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. A copy of that
license is included as LICENSE. You may obtain the original at:

    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

MODIFICATIONS (per Apache-2.0 section 4(b))
-------------------------------------------
The weights in data/weights.bin are derived from the ONNX bundle published at the
URL above, with two changes:

  1. Container format: the ONNX initializers are flattened into a single
     little-endian array, described by data/weights.txt. No values change.

  2. Precision: values are converted from float32 to IEEE binary16 (float16),
     halving the file from 9.12 MB to 4.56 MB. This is lossy. Measured end to
     end, the enhanced audio differs from the float32 reference by 75.5 dB
     SI-SDR -- above the ~67 dB ceiling a 16-bit WAV can represent, so the
     difference is not audible in a shipped file, but it is a real change and is
     stated here rather than implied to be exact.

Full-precision float32 weights can be regenerated from the upstream ONNX bundle
with tools/export_weights.py in the source repository.

